generate_caption.user_template:
Write an Instagram caption for a photo about: {topic}.
Day {day}, slot {slot}. Max 30 words. Add 2-3 relevant hashtags.
{mention_instruction}

generate_comment.user_template:
{author} posted: "{caption}"

Write a brief, authentic comment (under 100 characters).
{mention_instruction}

generate_news_commentary.user_template:
Your job is to present news articles to your audience in an engaging way. Respond ONLY with the tweet text - no explanations, no formatting notes. Here's a news article to share:

Title: {article_title}

Content: {article_text}

Write a brief, engaging Tweet to present this article to your followers. Be professional but engaging. Do NOT include hashtags or links - just your commentary on the article. Output ONLY the tweet text. Do not explain, summarize, quote the prompt, add preambles, or wrap it in markdown.

decide_follow.user_template:
User @{username} has the following bio: {bio}
Their recent posts are about: {topics}
Should you follow them? Reply ONLY with: FOLLOW or SKIP.

extract_article_topics.user_template:
Extract exactly 1 or 2 main topics from the article. Return ONLY the topics, separated by commas, no other text. Avoid stopwords and empty words. Extract 1-2 main topics from this article:

{article_text}

Topics (comma-separated):

extract_emotions.user_template:
Identify emotions from this text. Choose ONLY from: {emotion_list}

Text: "{text}"

Return emotions as comma-separated list:

infer_article_opinion.user_template:
Analyze this text and determine its stance on the topic '{topic}'.

Text excerpt:
{article_text}

What is the text's stance? Choose ONLY ONE from these options:
{opinion_options}

Your choice (ONE WORD ONLY):

evaluate_opinion_transition.user_template:
Topic: {topic}

Current opinion class: {current_label}
Author opinion class: {author_label}
Opinion scale: {opinion_scale}

Post:
{post_content}

If the post should move the current opinion one adjacent step toward the author, reply AGREE. If it should move one adjacent step away, reply DISAGREE. If it should stay in the same class, reply NEUTRAL.
